Stabilize onClick handlers in SpanTreeView to preserve React.memo (#2215)

`SpanTreeView` creates inline `onClick` lambdas per row on every render,
defeating `React.memo` on `SpanTreeRow` and `SpanTreeGroupRow`. Changing
selection re-renders the entire list instead of just affected rows.

### Changes

- **`SpanTreeView.tsx`**: Add a `useMemo` span-by-id map; refactor
`handleRowClick` to accept `spanId: string` and look up the span. Pass
the stable callback directly instead of inline closures.

```tsx
// Before — new function identity per row per render
onClick={() => handleRowClick(item.node.span)}

// After — single stable reference shared by all rows
onClick={handleRowClick}
```

- **`SpanTreeView.memo.test.tsx`**: New test renders 3 spans, changes
selection from span-1→span-3, asserts span-2 (unaffected) renders
exactly once. Fails without the fix, passes with it.

