<issue_title>[react-component-best-practices] SpanTreeView memoized rows
rerender due to unstable onClick props</issue_title>
<issue_description>## Impact
`SpanTreeView` passes new inline `onClick` functions to memoized row
components on every parent render, so `React.memo` cannot skip unchanged
rows. In traces with many rows, changing selection causes avoidable
full-list rerenders and visible UI jank.

## Reproduction Steps
1. Install dependencies:
   - `cd peek && npm ci`
2. Create this minimal failing test file at
`peek/tests/component/SpanTreeView.memo.repro.test.tsx` (full code
below).
3. Run:
- `cd peek && npm run -s test:unit --
tests/component/SpanTreeView.memo.repro.test.tsx`

## Expected vs Actual
**Expected:** only rows whose props changed should rerender when
`selectedSpanId` changes.

**Actual:** an unaffected row rerenders because `SpanTreeView` recreates
`onClick` lambdas per row, changing function identity and invalidating
memo.

Actual test failure output:

```text
FAIL  |dom| tests/component/SpanTreeView.memo.repro.test.tsx > SpanTreeView memo reproduction > re-renders unaffected rows when only selectedSpanId changes
AssertionError: expected 2 to be 1 // Object.is equality

- Expected
+ Received

- 1
+ 2

❯ tests/component/SpanTreeView.memo.repro.test.tsx:89:43
```

## Failing Test
```tsx
import React from "react";
import { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from "vitest";
import { render } from "`@testing-library/react`";

import type { Span } from "../../src/components/traces/traceUtils";

const rowRenderCounts = new Map(string, number)();

vi.mock("react-virtuoso", () => ({
  Virtuoso: ({ data, itemContent }: { data: unknown[]; itemContent: (index: number, item: unknown) => React.ReactNode }) => (
    (div){data.map((item, index) => (div key={index}){itemContent(index, item)}(/div))}(/div)
  ),
}));

vi.mock("../../src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/useSpanTree", () => ({
  useSpanTree: (spans: Span[]) => ({
    flatRows: spans.map((span) => ({
      type: "span" as const,
      node: { span, children: [], depth: 0 },
      expanded: false,
      hasChildren: false,
    })),
    searchMode: false,
    toggleExpand: vi.fn(),
    toggleGroup: vi.fn(),
    expandAll: vi.fn(),
    collapseAll: vi.fn(),
  }),
}));

vi.mock("../../src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/SpanTreeRow", () => ({
  SpanTreeRow: React.memo(function MockSpanTreeRow({
    node,
  }: {
    node: { span: { spanId: string } };
    selected: boolean;
    onClick: () => void;
  }) {
    rowRenderCounts.set(node.span.spanId, (rowRenderCounts.get(node.span.spanId) ?? 0) + 1);
    return (div data-testid={`row-\$\{node.span.spanId}`} /);
  }),
}));

vi.mock("../../src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/SpanTreeGroupRow", () => ({
  SpanTreeGroupRow: React.memo(() => (div data-testid="group-row" /)),
}));

vi.mock("../../src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/SpanTreeToolbar", () => ({
  default: () => null,
}));

import SpanTreeView from "../../src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/SpanTreeView";

function buildSpan(spanId: string): Span {
  return {
    traceId: "trace-1",
    spanId,
    parentSpanId: null,
    serviceName: "svc",
    name: `op-\$\{spanId}`,
    kind: "INTERNAL",
    durationUs: 100,
    status: "OK",
    timestamp: "2026-01-01T00:00:00.000Z",
    startTimeUs: spanId === "span-1" ? 1 : 2,
    attributes: {},
  };
}

describe("SpanTreeView memo reproduction", () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    rowRenderCounts.clear();
  });

  it("re-renders unaffected rows when only selectedSpanId changes", () => {
    const spans = [buildSpan("span-1"), buildSpan("span-2")];

    const { rerender } = render(
      (SpanTreeView spans={spans} showToolbar={false} selectedSpanId={"span-1"} /),
    );

    expect(rowRenderCounts.get("span-1")).toBe(1);
    expect(rowRenderCounts.get("span-2")).toBe(1);

    rerender((SpanTreeView spans={spans} showToolbar={false} selectedSpanId={"span-2"} /));

    expect(rowRenderCounts.get("span-2")).toBe(2);
    // Expected to stay 1 because row props are unchanged except unstable onClick identity.
    expect(rowRenderCounts.get("span-1")).toBe(1);
  });
});
```

## Evidence
- Memoized row components:
  - `peek/src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/SpanTreeRow.tsx:38`
- `peek/src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/SpanTreeGroupRow.tsx:38`
- Unstable inline callbacks passed from parent on every render:
- `peek/src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/SpanTreeView.tsx:167-170`
  - `peek/src/components/traces/span-tree-plugin/SpanTreeView.tsx:187`
- Duplicate check:
  - `/tmp/previous-findings.json` does not include this bug
- GitHub search for open duplicates in this repo returned 0 matches for
targeted queries

## Suggested Fix
Stabilize row click handlers (e.g., pass `handleRowClick` plus span
identity as separate props, or memoize callbacks by row key) so
unaffected rows preserve shallow-equal props ...

