Narrow ExplorePage selector to dashboard.timeRange to avoid spurious re-renders (#2216)

`ExplorePage` subscribed to the entire `dashboard` object but only read
`dashboard.timeRange`. Any dashboard mutation (e.g. parameter value
edits) replaced the `dashboard` reference and triggered a full re-render
of the Explore subtree.

### Changes

- **`ExplorePage.tsx`** — Select `s.dashboard.timeRange` instead of
`s.dashboard` in the `useDashboardEditorStore` selector; update all
downstream references from `dashboard.timeRange` → `timeRange`
- **New test** — `repro-explore-dashboard-selector-rerender.test.tsx`
asserts that `setParameterValue` does not cause a re-render when
`timeRange` is unchanged

```diff
- const { dashboard, setTimeRange } = useDashboardEditorStore(
+ const { timeRange, setTimeRange } = useDashboardEditorStore(
    useShallow((s) => ({
-     dashboard: s.dashboard,
+     timeRange: s.dashboard.timeRange,
      setTimeRange: s.setTimeRange,
    })),
  );
```

